Create an External Activation Target in Data Cloud

To publish segments to your external platform account, create an activation target. An external platform can have multiple activation targets, but you can attach only one activation target to an external platform account.

Only an Admin or Marketing Manager role can create an activation target for the Google Ads, Meta, and Amazon Ads platforms. If you’re using Google, you must have Admin access.

On the Activation Targets tab, click New.
Select an external activation platform, and click Next.
Enter a name and an optional description.
If the privacy type isn't set, update the external activation platform to include a privacy type.
Add the platform's account and login details, and click Next.
If you're using the Google Ads, Google DV360, LinkedIn, Meta, or Amazon Ads platform you’re redirected to their site to provide login details.
Grant access permissions to Data Cloud, and accept the terms of service.
You’re redirected to Data Cloud and provided the accounts that you have permission to upload audiences to.
Select the data space you want to associate your activation target with.
Select the Account Name and ID.
The selected data space determines which Account IDs are available to create a unique combination for single use.
For Amazon Ads, if you have access to both an Amazon DSP account and AMC instance, you’re prompted to select an account for each.
If you select both DSP and AMC for a new activation target, make sure that your accounts are linked in Amazon Ads. Then, you can view the DSP account performance data in the AMC instance.
If you're using a platform installed from AppExchange, enter your Account ID.
Each account ID is unique and you can use it for only one activation target.
Select the data space you want to associate your activation target with.
Click Save.
